feat: add 5-stage progress bar to process_chat (Task #7)

Every chat message now shows a live progress indicator while the bot
processes the reply.

## What was implemented

- At the start of `process_chat` a reply is sent immediately:
    ⬜⬜⬜⬜⬜ 思考中
- Five internal checkpoints advance the bar one block at a time:
    Stage 1 — after image analysis (or skipped for text-only)
    Stage 2 — after KB context is built
    Stage 3 — after memory context is built
    Stage 4 — after the AI chat call returns
    Stage 5 — just before the final reply is dispatched
- The bar is deleted before every exit path (text reply, image reply,
  all error/warning replies) so it never lingers.

## Implementation details

Three closures defined inside `process_chat`:
  `_prog(n)`       — builds the emoji string for n filled blocks out of 5
  `_bar_set(n)`    — edits the bar message silently (try/except)
  `_bar_delete()`  — deletes bar, sets _bar_msg=None (idempotent)

Initial bar send is wrapped in try/except — permission errors never break
chat flow. All bar edits/deletes are equally silent.

## Edge cases handled and fixed (post review)

- `image_failed + no user_text`: bar deleted before error reply, returns.
- `image_failed + user_text` (warning, non-terminal): bar stays alive so
  stages 4 and 5 still advance correctly; bar is cleaned up at final reply.
- `image_prompt + response_text` (pre-text + image path): bar stays visible
  during send_with_suggestions for pre-text, then advances to stage 5 during
  image generation, and is deleted right before the image reply.
- Text-only path: _bar_set(5) → _bar_delete() → send_with_suggestions.
- Image generation path: _bar_set(5) visible during generate_image,
  _bar_delete() just before the final image reply.
- Cloudflare key missing path: bar deleted before error reply.
- SuggestionButton: calls process_chat directly — inherits bar automatically.

## Deviations from plan

None. Exactly 5 stages, fixed "思考中" label, uniform across all paths.
Top-level try/finally (optional hardening) was not implemented to avoid
restructuring the entire 200-line function body.
